LAGOS – Yesterday, a Nigerian lawmaker, Funke Adedoyin passed on. Adedoyin, a member of the House of Representatives from Kwara State, died on Friday afternoon in Abuja at the age of 54. According to Razak Atunwa, a fellow House of Reps member from Kwara, her death is a big loss. The deceased, who is the daughter of famed Nigerian industrialist Samuel Adedoyin, had been battling cancer in the past few years according to Atunwa, chairman of House Judiciary Committee and governorship aspirant in Kwara. Among other things, Adedoyin was appointed as health minister by former President Olusegun Obasanjo during his first term between 1999-2003. She was also amongst a host of All Progressives Congress lawmakers who joined the Peoples Democratic Party in a mass defection earlier this year. SHOCKING STORY!!! After 9 Years Of Suffering From Weak Erection & Premature Ejaculation, 43 Year Old Man Finally Discovers The Solution That Mysteriously Jerk His Dead Manhood Back To Life, Increased His "Rod" Size, And Now Last 32 Minutes In Bed. Click HERE! 